        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 1 at 7:16PM PDT by NWS Sacramento CA</headline>
        <description>At 716 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Fisher, or 20 miles north of Shasta Dam, moving south at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lakehead, Sugarloaf, Fisher, O'brien, Lakehead-Lakeshore, Vollmers,
and Pollard Flat.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
